1
00:00:01,200 --> 00:00:04,800
"KÔKÔ KYÔSHI"

2
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:25,500
<i>The horoscope said that I should
go on a date this weekend.</i>

3
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:26,800
<i>Do you want to go with me?</i>

4
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:31,600
<i>- Our first date!
- If it rains, we should just cancel.</i>

5
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:33,800
<i>It worked!</i>

6
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:37,470
Using Cantor's diagonal argument
you are able to see that

7
00:00:37,470 --> 00:00:41,940
infinity reaches beyond
natural numbers.

8
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:14,540
<i>Stop it!</i>

9
00:01:14,540 --> 00:01:17,340
<i>Suicide just isn't the answer.</i>

10
00:01:17,340 --> 00:01:19,600
<i>Didn't I say I was here for you?</i>

11
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:22,400
<i>That I'd always be by your side?</i>

12
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:26,800
<i>- Really?
- Really.</i>

13
00:01:27,100 --> 00:01:31,290
<i>Darn! I almost had it too!</i>

14
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:10,100
<i>- I did it!</i>
- What?

15
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:14,500
It's the first time you called me!

16
00:02:18,300 --> 00:02:22,640
Why would you do something like that
to someone who's worried about you?

17
00:02:22,640 --> 00:02:25,900
I always wanted to try,
but I decided not to.

18
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:27,600
You thought it'd be a nuisance?

19
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:33,510
No. At the park you said you'd be
thinking about me all the time.

20
00:02:33,510 --> 00:02:37,420
- Did I really say that?
- You said you promised!

21
00:02:37,420 --> 00:02:40,550
Fine then... so why the problem?

22
00:02:40,550 --> 00:02:43,060
I'm always the one
who calls you.

23
00:02:43,060 --> 00:02:48,100
- Oh, the phone bill?
- That's not it!

24
00:02:48,100 --> 00:02:50,870
Well... I guess there's a bit of that.

25
00:02:50,870 --> 00:02:53,430
Next time just call and hang up.
I'll call you back.

26
00:02:53,430 --> 00:02:57,570
- Thank you.
- No problem.

27
00:02:57,570 --> 00:02:59,340
What was I trying to say again?

28
00:02:59,340 --> 00:03:02,010
You said it's always you that calls.

29
00:03:02,010 --> 00:03:05,410
Sorry I waited to see if
you'd call, but...

30
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:13,950
I was happy.

31
00:03:15,460 --> 00:03:18,400
I'm not about to kill myself.

32
00:03:22,230 --> 00:03:25,130
I'm more positive than before.

33
00:03:25,130 --> 00:03:29,100
- Stop yawning.
- Go on then.

34
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:35,040
I don't know how long I have to live,
but there's lots I have left to do.

35
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:36,510
Stuff you haven't done yet?

36
00:03:36,510 --> 00:03:40,810
Like eating really nice food.
You could pay for it.

37
00:03:40,810 --> 00:03:42,080
Me?

38
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:46,020
And going places I've never been.

39
00:03:46,020 --> 00:03:47,590
Also...

40
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:53,030
Oh! I forgot my phone!

41
00:03:53,030 --> 00:03:55,930
- At my place?
- I think so.

42
00:03:55,930 --> 00:03:59,000
We'll have to go back.

43
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:02,970
Just go ahead! We shouldn't be
at the station together anyway.

44
00:04:02,970 --> 00:04:06,830
You're right. Here's the key.

45
00:04:07,010 --> 00:04:10,000
I'll put it in your shoe box
at school.

46
00:04:13,380 --> 00:04:15,800
Also...

47
00:04:16,780 --> 00:04:21,760
The thing I want to do most...

48
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:27,390
<i>﻿At that time, there were differences
between us.</i>

49
00:04:27,390 --> 00:04:33,600
<i>﻿Like that carefree positive
energy of hers.</i>

50
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,170
I...

51
00:04:38,140 --> 00:04:40,110
I want to fall in love.

52
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:57,720
<i>I was always running
from the truth.</i>

53
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:11,570
I said it!

54
00:05:29,220 --> 00:05:32,060
- Excuse me!
- Welcome.

55
00:05:36,130 --> 00:05:39,500
I made a double!

